# Episode Data Workflow

## Episode Object Shape

Every episode in `src/config.ts` uses this structure:

```typescript
{
  title: "Episode N",        // "Episode 1" through "Episode N"
  guest: "Full Name",        // Guest's full name
  guestTitle: "Role",        // Job title or descriptor (see special cases below)
  guestCompany: "Company",   // Company/fund name — can be empty string ""
  xUrl?: string,             // X broadcast or post link (optional)
  youtubeUrl?: string,       // YouTube video or livestream link (optional)
}
```

- **Add new episodes at the top** of the `siteConfig.episodes` array
- Episode numbers are **auto-calculated** from array position — never hardcode them in the title logic
- At least one of `xUrl` or `youtubeUrl` should be present; having both shows two platform pills
- Play button defaults to **YouTube first**, X as fallback: `ep.youtubeUrl || ep.xUrl`

---

## Step-by-Step Process for Adding New Episodes

This is the exact workflow used in the April 2026 session to add episodes 7–11.

### Step 1 — Get Episode List from Notion

The Notion MCP tools must be chained — you can't jump straight to a query. The sequence is:

1. **`notion-fetch`** the Episodes database directly by ID:
   - Database ID: `3344613294668035aa4dd29efc7b4696`
   - This returns the database schema and a `<view url="view://...">` tag in the response

2. **`notion-query-database-view`** using the view URL from step 1:
   - View URL: `view://33446132-9466-817e-934f-000c3651e323`
   - Returns all episode rows with their fields

The `view://UUID` format is specific to the Notion MCP — it only appears after fetching the database. Don't try to construct it manually.

Each row contains: `Episode` (number), `Guest`, `Firm or Company`, `Select` (status), `Email`, `Date`.

Status values:
- `Podcast Recorded` — episode is done, safe to add to site
- `Podcast Episode Booked` — scheduled but not yet recorded
- `Pre-Interview Done` — onboarding complete, not yet recorded

### Step 2 — Get Guest Roles from Attio (if missing from Notion)

If `Firm or Company` or job title is blank in Notion, search Attio CRM:
- Search object: `people` (required — Attio searches are object-scoped)
- Query: guest's full name
- Check **both** `job_title` and `description` fields — `description` often has a richer LinkedIn-style bio with more accurate role info than `job_title`

**You can search multiple guests in parallel** — fire all Attio searches in a single message rather than sequentially. For 3 missing guests, 3 simultaneous `search-records` calls is correct.

### Step 3 — Get YouTube Links

Fetch both tabs of the YouTube channel:
- **Videos tab:** `https://www.youtube.com/@TheSuperlativePodcast/videos`
- **Live tab:** `https://www.youtube.com/@TheSuperlativePodcast/streams`

Match episode titles to guest names. Extract `watch?v=` URLs from page HTML (`ytInitialData` JSON).

Episodes only on YouTube will not have an `xUrl`. Episodes only on X will not have a `youtubeUrl`.

### Step 4 — Get X Links

X broadcast links are in the Notion **Podcast Artifacts** database or on the host's X profile (@thespeakerlisan). Format:
- Broadcasts: `https://x.com/i/broadcasts/XXXXXX`
- Posts: `https://x.com/thespeakerlisan/status/XXXXXXXXXX`

### Step 5 — Write the Config Entry

Add to the **top** of `siteConfig.episodes` in `src/config.ts`:

```typescript
{
  title: "Episode 12",
  guest: "Guest Name",
  guestTitle: "Managing Partner",
  guestCompany: "Fund Name",
  xUrl: "https://x.com/i/broadcasts/XXXXXX",
  youtubeUrl: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XXXXXX",
},
```

Leave out `xUrl` or `youtubeUrl` entirely (don't set to `""`) if that platform link isn't available yet.

### Step 6 — Verify

```bash
npx tsc --noEmit
```

No output = no type errors. Then commit and push to `main`.

