## Special Cases

### Guest is bigger than their company

If a guest's personal brand or reputation eclipses the company they're currently at, use `guestTitle` as a descriptor and leave `guestCompany` as `""`.

**Example — DaVinci Jeremie:**
```typescript
{
  guest: "DaVinci Jeremie",
  guestTitle: "Bitcoin Pioneer & Crypto Educator",
  guestCompany: "",   // intentionally blank
  xUrl: "...",
}
```

Don't list a startup or project name that would undersell who they are.

### Guest with multiple roles

Pack both into `guestTitle` when the company is the same umbrella:
```typescript
guestTitle: "Co-Founder, RaaSRocket & President",
guestCompany: "Unocoin",
```

Or list the primary company and note the secondary in the title:
```typescript
guestTitle: "Co-Founder",
guestCompany: "Loon",   // primary — Paytrie is secondary
```

### Link added later

If an episode goes live on a second platform after initial publish, just add the missing field to the existing entry — no other changes needed.

